    COPYRIGHT
    
    Copyright (C) 2005 and onwards by AmbieSense Limited, 
    and/or its subsidiaries and co-founders. AmbieSense Limited
    is an R&D-focused company incorporated in Scotland.

    PURPOSE OF THE SOFTWARE RELEASE
    
    The AmbieSense Context Software is for storing, retrieving, and matching 
    context information and meta-data for applications and services.    
    The theoretical foundations of this software have been published in various 
    scientific publications. 
     
    TARGET AUDIENCE
    
    This release has been made available for the general public to be able to 
    contribute and use e.g. for making ubiquitous and context-aware applications and 
    services, and to help in making such adaptive systems widespread in the society 
    to the benefit of application developers and organizations interested in 
    the retrieval and filtering context information and meta-data across a wide 
    spectrum of applications and services. A good starting point for understanding 
    the underlying foundations for this software, is to read: 
    
    PROPOSED READING
    
		Information Retrieval: Searching in the 21st Century
		Dr Ayse Goker (Editor), John Davies (Co-Editor)
		ISBN: 978-0-470-03363-0
		Available E-book as and hard-cover book
		320 pages
		December 2009
		Chapter: Context and Information Retrieval
	
	The AmbieSense Context Software Source Code is released as a 
	prototype software for research and development purposes 
	for anyone to use the way they want under the 
	the terms and conditions of the GPL version 3 license.

    ROADMAP TO IMPLEMENTATION
    
    This new initial version has been completely re-written with a simpler 
	SQL database in a datawarehouse style. The long-term goal is try to make it 
	a cloud-based and highly scalable solution that will use Solandra 
	as the storage solution.
	      
